race.comment: WRITTEN SCANDAL (7) raced wide without cover and couldn't quicken as required when beaten around three lengths over 1100m at Warwick Farm last start. Freshened up and this trip is far more suitable. Braith Nock back aboard is a tick - he is two-for-two aboard the mare. KILONOVA (8) raced on the pace but couldn't change gears in the heavy ground over 1100m at Rosehill last time out. Very fit now and a longer trip on a firmer track looks a good recipe for success. TITANIUM MISS (3) was left flat-footed and missed the frame when resuming at Rosehill recently. Yet to place in four first-up runs so the effort was forgivable. Will be far more effective over this trip at the second run back. MISS SPACEGIRL (4) is back from a 20-week break. Both first-up runs to date have been very good. Trialling well and should be right in the thick of things. PESCHIERA (6) has placed three from three at Canterbury and goes well fresh so this sets up nicely.
